extends layout.pug

block content
  h4 Finally choose the character that you're the most interested in!
  .characterDiv
    img#PokemonTrainer(src='https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/thumb/2/28/Pok%C3%A9mon_Trainer_%28solo%29_SSBU.png/300px-Pok%C3%A9mon_Trainer_%28solo%29_SSBU.png')
    h5 Pokemon Trainer
    button#summaryPokemonTrainer.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:left") 
      | Summary
    button#choosePokemonTrainer.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:right" data-name='PokemonTrainer') 
      | Choose
  .characterDiv
    img#Shulk(src='https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Shulk_SSBU.png/250px-Shulk_SSBU.png')
    h5 Shulk
    button#summaryShulk.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:left") 
      | Summary
    button#chooseShulk.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:right" data-name='Shulk') 
      | Choose
  .characterDiv
    img#Joker(src='https://www.ssbwiki.com/images/thumb/5/5c/Joker_SSBU.png/500px-Joker_SSBU.png')
    h5 Joker
    button#summaryJoker.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:left") 
      | Summary
    button#chooseJoker.btn.btn-dark(type='button' style="float:right" data-name='Joker') 
      | Choose

  #pokemonTrainerModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1', role='dialog', aria-labelledby='exampleModalLabel', aria-hidden='true')
    .modal-dialog(role='document')
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          h5#exampleModalLabel.modal-title Pokemon Trainer Summary
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal', aria-label='Close')
            span(aria-hidden='true') ×
        .modal-body
          p Pokemon Trainer makes for a mechanically unique character choice in Smash Bros. as the player does not control him as a playable combatant, but rather a set of three unique Pokémon that belong to him, only one of which partakes in the match at any given point. Each Pokemon has their own set of weight and abilities.
        .modal-footer
          button.btn.btn-dark(type='button' data-dismiss="modal") Cool!
  
  #shulkModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1', role='dialog', aria-labelledby='exampleModalLabel', aria-hidden='true')
    .modal-dialog(role='document')
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          h5#exampleModalLabel.modal-title Shulk Summary
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal', aria-label='Close')
            span(aria-hidden='true') ×
        .modal-body
          p Shulk is a medium character that can change his stats in the middle of a battle using his neutral speacial. He is the only fighter that can change his status during battle. His sword, the Monado, allows him to switch between five modes—Jump, Speed, Shield, Buster and Smash—which change his abilities for a short time.
        .modal-footer
          button.btn.btn-dark(type='button' data-dismiss="modal") Cool!
  
  #jokerModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1', role='dialog', aria-labelledby='exampleModalLabel', aria-hidden='true')
    .modal-dialog(role='document')
      .modal-content
        .modal-header
          h5#exampleModalLabel.modal-title Joker Summary
          button.close(type='button', data-dismiss='modal', aria-label='Close')
            span(aria-hidden='true') ×
        .modal-body
          p Joker is a medium-lightweight character with fast ground mobility, a quick fast fall and the ability to wall jump. He possesses fast frame data overall. He specializes in a mixed tricky/rushdown style gameplay, as the majority of his arsenal boasts powerful traits, though the range on his standard attacks is lacking without Arsene available.
        .modal-footer
          button.btn.btn-dark(type='button' data-dismiss="modal") Cool!
